<div data-type="exercise" id="fs-id1165042327384">
<div data-type="problem" id="fs-id1165042327386">
<p id="fs-id1165042327389">A patient&#8217;s pulse measures <math xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML" display="inline"><semantics><mrow><mrow><mtext>70 bpm, 80 bpm, then 120 bpm</mtext><mo>.</mo></mrow></mrow><annotation-xml encoding="MathML-Content"><mrow><mtext>70 bpm, 80 bpm, then 120 bpm</mtext><mo>.</mo></mrow></annotation-xml></semantics></math> To determine an accurate measurement of pulse, the doctor wants to know what value minimizes the expression <math xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML" display="inline"><semantics><mrow><mrow><msup><mrow><mrow><mo>(</mo><mrow><mi>x</mi><mo>&#8722;</mo><mn>70</mn></mrow><mo>)</mo></mrow></mrow><mn>2</mn></msup><mo>+</mo><msup><mrow><mrow><mo>(</mo><mrow><mi>x</mi><mo>&#8722;</mo><mn>80</mn></mrow><mo>)</mo></mrow></mrow><mn>2</mn></msup><mo>+</mo><msup><mrow><mrow><mo>(</mo><mrow><mi>x</mi><mo>&#8722;</mo><mn>120</mn></mrow><mo>)</mo></mrow></mrow><mn>2</mn></msup><mo>?</mo></mrow></mrow><annotation-xml encoding="MathML-Content"><mrow><msup><mrow><mrow><mo>(</mo><mrow><mi>x</mi><mo>&#8722;</mo><mn>70</mn></mrow><mo>)</mo></mrow></mrow><mn>2</mn></msup><mo>+</mo><msup><mrow><mrow><mo>(</mo><mrow><mi>x</mi><mo>&#8722;</mo><mn>80</mn></mrow><mo>)</mo></mrow></mrow><mn>2</mn></msup><mo>+</mo><msup><mrow><mrow><mo>(</mo><mrow><mi>x</mi><mo>&#8722;</mo><mn>120</mn></mrow><mo>)</mo></mrow></mrow><mn>2</mn></msup><mo>?</mo></mrow></annotation-xml></semantics></math> What value minimizes it?</p>
</div>
</div>
<div data-type="exercise" id="fs-id1165042647088">
<div data-type="problem" id="fs-id1165042647090">
<p id="fs-id1165042398959">In the previous problem, assume the patient was nervous during the third measurement, so we only weight that value half as much as the others. What is the value that minimizes <math xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML" display="inline"><semantics><mrow><mrow><msup><mrow><mrow><mo>(</mo><mrow><mi>x</mi><mo>&#8722;</mo><mn>70</mn></mrow><mo>)</mo></mrow></mrow><mn>2</mn></msup><mo>+</mo><msup><mrow><mrow><mo>(</mo><mrow><mi>x</mi><mo>&#8722;</mo><mn>80</mn></mrow><mo>)</mo></mrow></mrow><mn>2</mn></msup><mo>+</mo><mfrac><mn>1</mn><mn>2</mn></mfrac><msup><mrow><mrow><mo>(</mo><mrow><mi>x</mi><mo>&#8722;</mo><mn>120</mn></mrow><mo>)</mo></mrow></mrow><mn>2</mn></msup><mo>?</mo></mrow></mrow><annotation-xml encoding="MathML-Content"><mrow><msup><mrow><mrow><mo>(</mo><mrow><mi>x</mi><mo>&#8722;</mo><mn>70</mn></mrow><mo>)</mo></mrow></mrow><mn>2</mn></msup><mo>+</mo><msup><mrow><mrow><mo>(</mo><mrow><mi>x</mi><mo>&#8722;</mo><mn>80</mn></mrow><mo>)</mo></mrow></mrow><mn>2</mn></msup><mo>+</mo><mfrac><mn>1</mn><mn>2</mn></mfrac><msup><mrow><mrow><mo>(</mo><mrow><mi>x</mi><mo>&#8722;</mo><mn>120</mn></mrow><mo>)</mo></mrow></mrow><mn>2</mn></msup><mo>?</mo></mrow></annotation-xml></semantics></math></p>
</div>
<div data-type="solution" id="fs-id1165042318702">
<p id="fs-id1165042318704"><math xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML" display="inline"><semantics><mrow><mrow><mn>84</mn><mspace width="0.2em"/><mtext>bpm</mtext></mrow></mrow><annotation-xml encoding="MathML-Content"><mrow><mn>84</mn><mspace width="0.2em"/><mtext>bpm</mtext></mrow></annotation-xml></semantics></math></p>
